1
00:00:00,867 --> 00:00:02,633
<i>Congratulations!
The curse is gone!</i>

2
00:00:02,633 --> 00:00:05,500
<i>Our neighbors also did
the same thing.</i>

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:07,700
<i>- How are they now?
- They became a couple...</i>

4
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:09,200
<i> and got married.</i>

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,733
<i>They now have
five children!</i>

6
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:11,867
<i>- Huh?
- What?</i>

7
00:00:11,867 --> 00:00:15,300
<i>What if you two also
end up together?</i>

8
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,433
<i>Jade, I have
something to tell you.</i>

9
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Miss Jade!</i>

10
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,400
<i>This is you and
Mister Kiko.</i>

11
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:23,000
<i>You and your boyfriend
look cute together.</i>

12
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,167
<i> No, he's not my boyfriend.</i>

13
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:26,467
<i> He's my best friend.</i>

14
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:30,033
<i>Prepare for our next
meeting with Uncle Ronald.</i>

15
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:33,033
<i> - We have another meeting?
- Shh. Quiet.</i>

16
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:33,933
<i> Why are you shushing me?</i>

17
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,233
<i>Because this is a
personal meeting.</i>

18
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:38,000
<i>Sari, promise me you won't
tell anyone else.</i>

19
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:40,133
<i> Did you find out anything?</i>

20
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:42,567
<i>I got Sandro Soliman's
previous home address.</i>

21
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,500
<i> Okay, send it to me.</i>

22
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:48,567
- Sari.
- Oh.

23
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:51,167
Martin is still
in the restroom.

24
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:52,300
Ah...

25
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:54,633
It's you I wanted
to talk to.

26
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:59,200
I know that Martin is expecting
me to say yes now.

27
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,200
[CHUCKLES]

28
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:02,433
Sari...

29
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:04,733
What do you like
about Martin?

30
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,700
Sorry?

31
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:07,567
[CHUCKLES]

32
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,233
I just want to know
what you like about him

33
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,567
that made you become
his girlfriend.

34
00:01:12,567 --> 00:01:14,067
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

35
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:16,233
I-- W-- What?

36
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,567
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

37
00:01:17,567 --> 00:01:19,067
Don't be shy.

38
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:20,833
Tell me.

39
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:23,433
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:25,467
He gave me an umbrella.

41
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:28,833
An umbrella?

42
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,233
[CHUCKLES]

43
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:31,333
That's it?

44
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:35,833
When I first met him,
it was raining.

45
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:36,967
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]
- [RAIN POURING]

46
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:39,300
We still didn't know each
other that time.

47
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,567
He saw me getting
drenched in rain,

48
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,500
so he handed me
an umbrella.

49
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:47,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:50,067
It might not be
a big deal to others.

51
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:54,667
But for me, it showed
that he's considerate,

52
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:57,100
whether it be about
business or personal stuff.

53
00:01:57,767 --> 00:01:58,833
Hmm.

54
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:03,767
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

55
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:10,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:05,833
- Well?
- What is it now?

57
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:08,400
Come on, tell me.
How did it go?

58
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:11,700
Did you tell her or will you
keep it to yourself forever?

59
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:14,433
We didn't talk about anything,
okay?

60
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:17,233
Oh come on, bro.

61
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,567
What's with you?

62
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:20,733
You mean you went there
for nothing?

63
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,233
I'll do it next time.

64
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,800
Yeah, right. Let's see where
that will take you.

65
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,567
Hold on. Why are you
making this about me?

66
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:30,300
You also have something
to tell me, right?

67
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,600
What is it?

68
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:35,467
You're really good at changing
topics, aren't you?

69
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:37,667
What is it?

70
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:40,867
- Bro, brace yourself.
- What?

71
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:43,633
- I'm going to be a manager!
- Ow!

72
00:03:43,633 --> 00:03:45,200
- Wow!
- Yes!

73
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,833
- That was fast. Where?
- Yeah.

74
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:50,533
Trixie is opening up
a new bar,

75
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:53,733
and she wants me
to manage it.

76
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,800
Oh, that's good.
And it's just nearby.

77
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:58,300
- Yes. I know, right?
- We can still see each other.

78
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,467
When are you starting?

79
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,233
Well, after she buys
the place.

80
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:05,500
Oh, it's not sure yet?

81
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,700
I'd say a fifty-fifty chance.

82
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,433
Oh, dear.

83
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:14,267
You should've made
it clear.

84
00:04:14,267 --> 00:04:16,600
I said "I'm going to be
a manager."

85
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,433
"Going."

86
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,800
Not now, but in the future.

87
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,767
Yes, but when?

88
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:24,933
When the bar is ready.

89
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:28,533
- It's-- Yes, I'll manage it.
- When it's ready.

90
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:31,933
Maybe you should
manage yourself.

91
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:33,933
Do you have
a manager already? [CHUCKLES]

92
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:36,333
You could be
a celebrity. [CHUCKLES]

93
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,833
- Sari.
- Oh. Yes?

94
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:49,933
Sandwich?

95
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:52,833
I've got banana chips too.

96
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:56,767
- I'll have banana chips.
- There's coffee too.

97
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:58,700
Oh. I prefer iced coffee.

98
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,967
Just kidding. [CHUCKLES]

99
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,400
Where did you
and Martin go?

100
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,500
Oh, we had a meeting
with Uncle Ronald.

101
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,933
- Oh.
- Mmm.

102
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:07,900
- Uncle?
- Mm-hmm.

103
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,600
He's Martin's uncle?

104
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,900
No, he's the father
of Sir Martin's friend.

105
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:15,600
Hmm. A personal meeting.

106
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,967
Nope.

107
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:20,700
Sir Martin is looking
for investors.

108
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,267
Investors for what?

109
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,300
[LUNA] We just had a team
building and you do this?!

110
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,433
[MARTIN] What are you
talking about?!

111
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:33,700
[LUNA] Drop the act, Martin!
You're busted.

112
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:37,333
You did that so you could
get the upper hand.

113
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:40,400
This just shows you have no
idea how to run a business.

114
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,433
Having business partners
will help us get money.

115
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:44,933
And you're manipulating
it to your favor!

116
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:48,000
Martin, Luna,
what's going on?

117
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,400
Why are you two
fighting again?

118
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:52,733
Your brother is getting
investors without our knowledge.

119
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:55,400
I wouldn't have known if Sari
hadn't slipped up.

120
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,767
What? Is that true, Martin?

121
00:05:57,767 --> 00:06:00,000
Yes, I was talking
to a possible investor.

122
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,467
Why didn't you tell me
and Leon about it?

123
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:04,433
Because it's not a done deal.

124
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:05,833
He still hasn't decided yet.
Ask Sari.

125
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,633
Do you honestly think
I'll still believe you?

126
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:10,367
All you do
is attack me.

127
00:06:10,367 --> 00:06:12,933
Why don't you try to
understand what I'm doing?

128
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:15,133
I'm just protecting
our family's interest!

129
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:17,833
And I'm protecting
the hotel!

130
00:06:18,567 --> 00:06:20,700
This hotel is my family!

131
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,833
Our family doesn't
have money,

132
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:24,767
and you, Almazans, aren't
doing anything

133
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:26,533
to help get
more money.

134
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:28,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:30,967
Don't you get it, Luna?

136
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:34,433
We have to pay the
bank loan urgently.

137
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:37,067
As general manager, shouldn't
that be your concern

138
00:06:37,067 --> 00:06:39,367
instead of your
family's interests?!

139
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:42,600
I promised Dad I'd do
everything for our family,

140
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:44,467
and that includes this hotel.

141
00:06:44,467 --> 00:06:47,800
I won't let you and your family
get full control of this hotel!

142
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:55,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:04,700
- Tea?
- [KEYBOARD CLICKING]

144
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:05,967
Or sympathy?

145
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:09,400
What?

146
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,367
Are you sure about
the bar business?

147
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:13,733
Yes, Martin.

148
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:16,633
I just have a small problem,
but I can handle it.

149
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,267
Do you need my help?

150
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:19,867
[TRIXIE CLICKS TONGUE]
No, I got it.

151
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:22,233
You already have
enough on your plate.

152
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:27,267
Actually, I should be
the one helping you.

153
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,033
That's why I'm here,

154
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:31,000
to help you
when you need a breather.

155
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,767
I mean, you and Luna were
shouting at each other earlier.

156
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,033
[INHALES DEEPLY]

157
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:40,667
Luna's only like that,
because she's threatened by me.

158
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:42,033
She knows I should be the GM,

159
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:44,467
and I can do so much
of a better job than her.

160
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,567
True.

161
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:50,433
But you guys are starting
to get along, right?

162
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:54,433
And your move to
talk to Uncle Ronald?

163
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:55,733
That was a bit sneaky.

164
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:57,300
[SCOFFS] Fine.

165
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,600
It started that way.

166
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,733
I wanted to gain a partner,

167
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:02,733
so my siblings and I
could benefit from them.

168
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:06,300
[MARTIN] But right now,
my priority

169
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:08,467
is paying off our debt
to the bank,

170
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:10,300
so we don't lose Hotel 88.

171
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,867
Okay.

172
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:17,733
So, what's your plan now?

173
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:19,967
Will you stop talking
to Uncle Ronald?

174
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:21,667
Huh? Why?

175
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,067
Why would I do that?

176
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:24,900
Martin.

177
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:28,367
You and Luna are clashing
because of that.

178
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:30,400
So, if Luna and I are okay,

179
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,033
will that pay off our bank debt?

180
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:33,733
No.

181
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:34,800
But...

182
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:36,867
...come on, Martin.

183
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:38,733
Business is business, Trixie.

184
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:40,033
You should know that by now.

185
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,500
Don't worry about me.

186
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:51,067
I can stand by by decisions.

187
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:54,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,333
I know.

189
00:08:56,533 --> 00:08:58,367
I believe in you.

190
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:02,433
But, Martin,
you need to tell Gio.

191
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,867
[TRIXIE] All your siblings
need to know about this.

192
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,533
Leave it to me, Trixie.

193
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:14,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:16,833
Martin, are you okay?

195
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:20,033
Be honest. There's something
off about you.

196
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:22,800
Why wouldn't be I okay?

197
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,600
Martin, if this is about you

198
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,400
trying to prove
something to Dad...

199
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:29,367
Trixie.

200
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,367
I'm fine.

201
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,100
Okay.

202
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:39,900
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

203
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:43,700
So, Ma, you'll be
all alone in that house.

204
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:45,000
Are you okay with that?

205
00:09:46,033 --> 00:09:48,767
[GEORGIA]<i> What if I say
</i> I don't agree with this?

206
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:55,900
Ma, you know,
out of all the moms,

207
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,800
you're not clingy at all.

208
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:58,767
[LAUGHS]

209
00:09:58,767 --> 00:09:59,733
<i> Excuse me.</i>

210
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:02,033
<i>I'm the most
understanding mom ever.</i>

211
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:04,100
<i>I haven't seen you two
for so long,</i>

212
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:06,467
<i>and I only receive
messages from you,</i>

213
00:10:06,467 --> 00:10:07,700
<i> have I ever complained?</i>

214
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,033
<i> No, right?</i>

215
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:10,633
<i>That's why I'm the
most understanding</i>

216
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:11,900
<i> Mother of the Year.</i>

217
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:13,033
<i> Thank you.</i>

218
00:10:13,033 --> 00:10:14,000
Yes, Ma.

219
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,633
You're the most
understanding mom ever.

220
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:21,467
<i>And besides, you two
are adults already.</i>

221
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:24,467
<i>As long as you don't cheat,
you don't steal,</i>

222
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:27,433
<i>you don't do drugs, and
you don't kill people,</i>

223
00:10:27,433 --> 00:10:28,767
<i> I'm fine.</i>

224
00:10:28,767 --> 00:10:30,033
<i>- I'm happy with that.
- But...</i>

225
00:10:30,967 --> 00:10:34,033
Ma, I can't help but notice
and mention it.

226
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:35,567
It's like...

227
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,567
...your hair's so perfect, Ma.

228
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,067
I noticed it when
the call started.

229
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:40,933
- [KIKO GIGGLES]

230
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,800
- What's happening?
<i> - Uh...</i>

231
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,733
[CHESCA] I think Mommy
has a new boyfriend.

232
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:46,167
You've got a new
boyfriend, don't you, Ma?

233
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:47,933
That's the reason why
you don't want us there.

234
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:49,733
<i> Uh...</i>

235
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,900
Let us see your nails, Ma.
Come on.

236
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:53,933
Let us see!

237
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:55,000
<i> Why?</i>

238
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,200
What's wrong with you two?

239
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,700
My goodness.

240
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,900
Fine. Here.

241
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,700
<i> - We knew it!</i> [GIGGLES]
- Yeah!

242
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,767
<i>Ma, I'm not good at
giving manicures.</i>

243
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,567
<i>But I know what
that color means.</i>

244
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:09,700
<i>Ma, you usually get that color
when you like a new guy.</i>

245
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:12,200
Hold on, kids. Calm down.

246
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,133
He's only courting me.

247
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:16,933
And if he fools me, he'll go
straight to jail, because--

248
00:11:16,933 --> 00:11:18,200
<i> Ma, is it the Captain?</i>

249
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,767
Your new boyfriend
is the Captain, Ma?

250
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:22,833
<i> Shush! Watch your mouth.</i>

251
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,567
<i> The Captain's married!</i>

252
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:27,533
<i>It's Elmer, the guy
who works for him.</i>

253
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,867
<i> He's single.</i>

254
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:30,667
[KIKO] Ma, just be careful.

255
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,700
And if that man ever hurts you,

256
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:35,233
I'll bring my two brothers,
and get back at him.

257
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:36,200
Mhm-hmm.

258
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:37,933
<i> Of course.</i>

259
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:42,167
<i>Thank you,
my very protective eldest son.</i>

260
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,667
No, but seriously.

261
00:11:44,667 --> 00:11:46,267
Let's be serious for a while.

262
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,133
Don't worry about me, kids.

263
00:11:49,133 --> 00:11:50,633
I'm doing fine here.

264
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:52,767
Leave our vegetable store to me.

265
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:55,000
I'm happy to see
you two stick together.

266
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:57,967
[GEORGIA]
<i> But promise me one thing.</i>

267
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,533
<i> No matter what happens...</i>

268
00:12:00,933 --> 00:12:01,900
No matter what happens,

269
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,200
always remember to
take care of yourselves,

270
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,800
and each other, okay?

271
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:09,900
[KIKO] Of course, Ma.

272
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:11,733
I'll take care of this one.

273
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,100
<i> I'll take care of Kiko, Ma,</i>

274
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,033
<i>especially when
he's causing trouble.</i>

275
00:12:16,867 --> 00:12:18,767
[GEORGIA] I miss you, kids.

276
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,567
- I miss you, Ma.
- I miss you, Ma.

277
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,967
- Love you.
- I love you.

278
00:12:22,567 --> 00:12:24,133
Sir, please. Sir.

279
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:25,933
Sir.

280
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:27,200
- Hello. Good evening.
- Good evening.

281
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,833
Sir, please? [CRIES]

282
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,200
- Sir.
- Wait.

283
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,633
Don't close that room yet.

284
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:32,700
Okay, sir.

285
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:34,667
Come with me.

286
00:12:34,667 --> 00:12:35,633
Sir.

287
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:37,033
Tell me what it is!

288
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:39,033
Because I don't want our
guests outside to hear

289
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:41,600
just how incompetent the
people who work here are!

290
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:46,033
Sir, I didn't mean to
tell Miss Luna about Sir Ronald.

291
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:47,967
I told you that
was a secret, right?!

292
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,833
I forgot, sir.
I'm so sorry.

293
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:50,967
[MARTIN SCOFFS]

294
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:54,300
Is that all you want to say?

295
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:56,067
Yes.

296
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:58,067
I think we need
some time apart.

297
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,200
What, sir? "Time apart?"

298
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,100
[MARTIN] Yes. Leave.

299
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:06,000
- Leave!
- [GASPS]

300
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:13,033
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS MOVING AWAY]

301
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:27,000
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

302
00:13:44,733 --> 00:13:51,000
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:55,900
#22 RUCIO ST.
COSTA VIDA

304
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:06,000
[BUZZER RINGS]

305
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:14,800
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

306
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,767
[GATE CLINKS]

307
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:29,067
[GATE CREAKING]

308
00:14:31,967 --> 00:14:33,767
[GATE CREAKING]

309
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:41,333
[GATE CONTINUES
CREAKING DISTANTLY]

310
00:14:43,033 --> 00:14:50,000
[MUSIC CONTINUES, SWELLS]

311
00:14:55,200 --> 00:15:00,600
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

312
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:04,833
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

313
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,133
[JUSTIN WHISPERS] Hey, Juan!
Juan!

314
00:15:08,133 --> 00:15:09,333
What are you doing here?

315
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:11,867
My brother doesn't know
I'm here. I just followed him.

316
00:15:12,633 --> 00:15:14,133
Your brother is here?

317
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:15,333
What are you? The lookout?

318
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,200
You're accomplices.

319
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,200
What brings you
to my dad's house?

320
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,867
I don't even know!

321
00:15:20,867 --> 00:15:22,300
I didn't know this
was your house!

322
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:26,900
You won't get anything out
of my brother if you see him.

323
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,700
I know my brother,
he's stubborn.

324
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,200
You won't get
anything out of him

325
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:34,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,767
- Leon.
- Shh!

327
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,367
[GATE CREAKS]

328
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:44,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,233
Don't follow my brother.

330
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:52,833
Want to find out
where your dad is

331
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,267
and what my brother knows?

332
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,133
l'll help you.

333
00:15:58,067 --> 00:15:59,733
I'm an Almazan.

334
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:01,600
I have a lot of connections!

335
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,067
You won't need Leon anymore.

336
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:10,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

337
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:18,167
- [MUSIC BOX PLAYING]
- [MARTIN] All you do is attack!

338
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:20,733
Why don't you try to understand
<i> what I'm doing?!</i>

339
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:22,633
[LUNA] Because I'm protecting
our family's interest!

340
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:24,267
[MARTIN] And I'm protecting
the hotel's interests!

341
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:26,767
<i>This hotel is my family.
And you Almazans...</i>

342
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:28,200
<i>all you ever do
is attack people!</i>

343
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,067
<i>You never do anything
to help us around!</i>

344
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:33,167
[LUNA]<i> I'm not going
</i> to let you down, Dad.

345
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:36,800
<i>I won't let the
past get in my way.</i>

346
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:43,800
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:16:49,367 --> 00:16:51,300
[EXHALES]

348
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:09,867
Luna.

349
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:13,067
What are we doing here
in Edward's place?

350
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:18,100
When you're done,
could you serve it to them?

351
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,333
Luna?

352
00:17:22,433 --> 00:17:24,100
- Hey, Dad.
- [ANDY] Hey, bud.

353
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:27,733
- Hey, Luna.
- Uncle Andy.

354
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,333
[SMOOCHES]

355
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:30,933
- Uncle, hello.
- Jade.

356
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:32,800
- Nice seeing you again.
- Nice to see you again.

357
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,933
Let's do it, Uncle.

358
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:37,767
Really? You know,
that's wonderful news.

359
00:17:37,767 --> 00:17:39,433
I'm more than willing
to help you with the hotel.

360
00:17:42,967 --> 00:17:44,433
Ah...

361
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:46,000
Sorry?

362
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,300
H-help?

363
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,867
Ah... Luna,
what does Uncle mean?

364
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:55,733
[EDWARD] Didn't Luna say that...

365
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:59,700
we'll invest in Hotel 88?

366
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:04,133
Partner?

367
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,200
[JADE] Luna, you were
looking for a partner?

368
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:10,700
You knew about this?

369
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,733
- Jade...
- Are you doing this

370
00:18:15,733 --> 00:18:18,033
because of what you
fought about with Martin?

371
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:19,133
No, Jade.

372
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:21,167
We've been talking about this
for some time now.

373
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,333
Um...

374
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,967
Luna, I think it's best to talk
to your siblings first.

375
00:18:25,967 --> 00:18:27,500
[CHUCKLES] It's okay,
Uncle Andy.

376
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,167
If I explain this to them,

377
00:18:29,167 --> 00:18:31,767
I'm sure we'll all have
the same decision.

378
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:35,300
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

379
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:38,133
[ANDY] Okay, then.
As long as, uh...

380
00:18:38,133 --> 00:18:39,867
we're on the same page.

381
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:41,900
Just let me know when
we will sign

382
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:44,133
so we can inform
our lawyers.

383
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:46,233
And, uh, Jade,
I understand your concerns.

384
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:47,833
You have nothing
to worry about.

385
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:49,867
Edward will be your partner,

386
00:18:49,867 --> 00:18:52,267
as he will be handling
everything on our side.

387
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:53,400
Okay?

388
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,800
Thank you, Tito. I have also
spoken to our lawyers.

389
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,333
They will just call you.

390
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,100
[ANDY] Alright, good.
Exciting times ahead.

391
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:03,433
Our families will finally
become business partners.

392
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,833
[ANDY] Alright?
I'll see you later.

393
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:12,833
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,933
You got so mad at Martin
for talking to an investor.

395
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:19,833
But you were talking to one too.

396
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:22,200
Luna, you knew we
would fight about this.

397
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,800
[LUNA] Jade, they did it first.

398
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,267
I'm just fighting back.

399
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,433
Let's go.

400
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,000
Edward.

401
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:40,933
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

402
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:45,067
So this is your father's house.

403
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:50,067
Are you doing this
to hide the truth from me?

404
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:53,400
What truth?

405
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:57,167
That your brother has something
to do with Papa's disappearance.

406
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:00,467
Is that what you think of us?

407
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:01,467
Maybe it's Leon,

408
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:06,067
or you,
or your entire family.

409
00:20:06,067 --> 00:20:08,667
I just know you were involved
in Papa's disappearance.

410
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:11,600
You have no proof that
my family did anything.

411
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:15,000
But I know your father
did something.

412
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:19,000
Someone had him investigated.

413
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,033
It says here that he was
Uncle Mike's former contractor.

414
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:24,000
He was the one
who set fire to Hotel 88.

415
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

416
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,367
<i>"...intentional in nature
and consistent with arson."</i>

417
00:20:28,367 --> 00:20:30,100
"...consistent with intentional
<i> fire-setting behavior."</i>

418
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:37,167
Arson!

419
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:38,600
It wasn't an accident.

420
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,700
That's not true.

421
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:45,033
Why should I believe you?

422
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:47,567
You and your brother
are messing with me!

423
00:20:47,567 --> 00:20:51,367
I swear, Leon doesn't know
I'm doing this!

424
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:53,267
We are both looking for answers!

425
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:56,400
You want to know what my brother
had to do with your father?

426
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,700
That's the same question
they refuse to answer!

427
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:02,000
But, fine!

428
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Hit me!

429
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,700
But just to remind you,

430
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,300
you've been following
Leon for days

431
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,300
and you've come up
empty handed.

432
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:12,367
But now, you've learned
something from me.

433
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,633
So tell me,

434
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:17,033
was it me or my brother?

435
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:21,500
You're the only Almazan
who can help me right now.

436
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,733
But don't push my limits.

437
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:25,067
If I find out

438
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:28,100
you really are responsible
for Papa's disappearance,

439
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:31,200
you will all pay!

440
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:35,767
And that includes
all of your siblings.

441
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:41,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

442
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,133
[LINE RINGING]

443
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:46,133
Jade, where's Justin?

444
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:48,567
I don't know.
He's not answering my calls.

445
00:21:48,567 --> 00:21:50,267
He is unbelievable.

446
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,200
Luna.

447
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,300
We shouldn't make decisions
when we're angry or emotional.

448
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:57,567
Leon, Uncle Andy and I
already made a deal before.

449
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:01,600
Then you're no different
than Martin!

450
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,700
I told Luna the same thing,
Leon.

451
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:05,567
- I don't care.
- [LEON SCOFFS]

452
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:07,267
If we are going
to hire a new investor

453
00:22:07,267 --> 00:22:08,600
or partner for Hotel 88,

454
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,300
it should come from us.

455
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,433
It should be Uncle Andy.

456
00:22:12,433 --> 00:22:13,333
Luna...

457
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:16,267
[LUNA] Uncle Andy
is the right choice.

458
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:19,600
Martin hasn't sealed the deal
with his investor yet, right?

459
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,233
But we need to
talk to them first.

460
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:25,800
Martin said he's protecting
the interest of the hotel.

461
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,267
If that is the case,

462
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:29,600
then he shouldn't turn down
the investment of the Arellanos.

463
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:36,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

464
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,300
<i> Welcome to Hotel 88, sir!</i>

465
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:48,200
<i>The hotel that has witnessed
the secret stares of love.</i>

466
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,100
<i> Why do you feel insecure?</i>

467
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:51,133
<i>She's up here,
I'm way down here.</i>

468
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:52,667
<i>I can feel sparks between
you and Sir Kiko, Miss Jade.</i>

469
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,200
<i> I can feel it in my fingers,</i>

470
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,667
<i> and in my hair...</i>

471
00:22:56,767 --> 00:22:58,867
<i> in your heart!</i>

472
00:22:58,867 --> 00:23:00,733
[SQUEALING]

473
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:03,367
<i> Finish what you started.</i>

474
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:05,567
<i> Don't get his hopes up.</i>

475
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:07,300
<i>But you're flirting
with a guest!</i>

476
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:10,700
<i>I don't care if
you do this outside,</i>

477
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,867
<i>but don't you ever do it
here in the hotel!</i>

478
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:16,233
<i>So, you're going to run
away with me?</i>

479
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:17,900
<i>So you can leave behind
the negativity</i>

480
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:20,200
<i> that is making you sad.</i>

481
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,600
<i>I don't know if I still want
him to be our hotel partner.</i>

482
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:23,700
<i> I have a bad feeling.</i>

483
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:26,600
<i>We need him.
We're making him our partner.</i>

484
00:23:27,533 --> 00:23:29,633
<i>- A map of Hotel 88?
- What's that?</i>

485
00:23:29,633 --> 00:23:30,867
<i> I'm one step closer.</i>

486
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:34,933
<i> I'll access the places
</i>I've never been to at Hotel 88.

487
00:23:34,933 --> 00:23:37,167
<i>If I didn't succeed
at first,</i>

488
00:23:37,167 --> 00:23:38,633
<i> now I will.</i>

